cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a model for classification tasks using sparseness as a regularizer in neural networks. This topic is closely related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, which are covered by the cs.LG and cs.AI sub-categories. The use of sparseness in neural networks also involves the study of neuronal transfer functions, which falls under the cs.NE sub-category. The experiments conducted in the paper involve image classification, which is a common application of computer vision, covered by the cs.CV sub-category. Finally, the paper also discusses the theoretical aspects of sparseness-enforcing projection, which can be related to natural language processing and information retrieval, covered by the cs.CL sub-category.
